Elytra fused, convex, ovoid, widening to midlength, then narrowing, maximum width in midlength. Disc symmetrically convex without any distinct collar-like depression. Humeri distinct, weakly rounded without bevelling, elytral base without any distinct rim. Elytra margined with a narrow rim, regularly and softly punctured longwise, without widening. Striae shallower (than in 

C. strachani

), strial punctuation very soft, almost indistinct. Intervals almost flat, softly and densely punctured in five to six lines. Intervals with distinct isodiametric microsculpure among punctuation. Elytra sparsely covered with dark setae which are shorter than those covering the pronotum.
